HEADWORD: Terebene
<hw>Ter"e*bene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A polymeric modification of terpene, obtained as a white
crystalline camphorlike substance; -- called also
<altname>camphene</altname>. By extension, any one of a group of related
substances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

